concepts:
- concept_id: C-001
  name: ProjectRegistry
  definition: Scans projects.root_dir on startup and explicit refresh. Builds a registry
    of valid projects from projectid marker files. Resolves project_id to a canonical
    project root path. Enforces path containment invariants before any mount operation.
  properties:
  - Rejects duplicates; all conflicting projects disabled until operator fixes conflict
  - Rejects symlink escapes, relative traversal, and paths outside projects.root_dir
  - Resolution is read-only; registry is built from marker files only
  - require_uuid4_id config flag enforces UUID4 format on marker id field
  - allow_nested_projects=false (default) rejects nested project markers
  source_ranges:
  - start: 83
    end: 100
  - start: 101
    end: 131
  - start: 132
    end: 167
- concept_id: C-002
  name: ProjectMarker
  definition: Fixed-format file named exactly "projectid" at the root of a project
    directory. Contains JSON with required fields id (UUID4) and description (string).
    mcp_terminal may only read this file; it must not rename, reconfigure, or rewrite
    it.
  properties:
  - Filename is fixed to "projectid" and is not configurable
  - Must be valid JSON
  - id field must be present; UUID4 format enforced when require_uuid4_id is true
  - description field is required
  - Directory name is not the project identity; the id field is
  source_ranges:
  - start: 108
    end: 131
- concept_id: C-003
  name: SandboxPolicy
  definition: Validates every execution request against configured security rules
    before any container is created. Enforces cwd containment, mode restrictions,
    network mode allowlist, image profile allowlist, and command policy. Rejects forbidden
    runtime options unconditionally.
  properties:
  - cwd must be relative and resolve inside /workspace
  - 'Supported modes: read_only (default), workspace_write, scratch_write'
  - 'Network modes: none (default), package_registry; open is forbidden in MVP'
  - Image profile must be from server-side allowlist; caller cannot provide image
    names
  - Forbidden runtime options include --privileged, --pid host, --network host, --cap-add
    SYS_ADMIN, and Docker socket volume mount
  - Command policy denies empty argv, NUL bytes, absolute executables outside safe
    PATH
  source_ranges:
