- concept_id: C-004
  name: TerminalSession
  definition: Scoped execution context identified by the pair (project_id, session_id).
    session_id is a UUID4 generated at creation time. Owns a session directory under
    .terminals/<session_id>/. Has a TTL based on last_activity_at. Activity includes
    session creation, command start/finish, output read, output search, and explicit
    metadata access.
  properties:
  - One project may have multiple independent sessions
  - session_id is UUID4 and is validated on every terminal_run call
  - terminal_run does not create sessions implicitly
  - TTL is computed from last_activity_at
  - Expired completed/failed/stopped sessions may be deleted after TTL
  - Running sessions may be deleted only with an explicit force flag
  source_ranges:
  - start: 461
    end: 495
  - start: 557
    end: 580
  - start: 782
    end: 860
  - start: 1141
    end: 1181
- concept_id: C-005
  name: SessionStore
  definition: Creates and manages session directories under .terminals/<session_id>/.
    Enforces TTL cleanup policy. Protects running sessions from deletion unless force
    flag is explicitly provided. Ensures .terminals/ is gitignored inside the project
    directory.
  properties:
  - Creates .terminals/<session_id>/ on terminal_session_create
  - Deletes session directory and all contents on terminal_delete
  - Cleanup interval is configurable; never deletes running jobs without force
  - .terminals/ must be added to project .gitignore
  - terminal_delete with project_id scopes deletion to that project only
  - terminal_delete without project_id deletes across all known projects
  source_ranges:
  - start: 461
    end: 495
  - start: 725
    end: 760
  - start: 782
    end: 860
  - start: 1141
    end: 1181
- concept_id: C-006
  name: CommandRecord
  definition: Single entry in history.jsonl representing one executed command. Contains
    seq, job_id, project_id, session_id, timestamp, execution_kind, command (for shell
    kind), argv (for argv kind), resolved_argv (always), cwd, mode, network, image_profile,
    status, exit_code, timed_out, stdout_file, stderr_file.
  properties:
  - execution_kind is either "shell" or "argv" and is mandatory
  - 'For shell kind: command is non-null string, argv is null'
  - 'For argv kind: command is null, argv is non-null array'
  - resolved_argv is always present and contains the actual argv passed to the runtime
  - seq is a session-local monotonic integer
  - Appended to history.jsonl; file is append-only
  source_ranges:
  - start: 496
    end: 548
- concept_id: C-007
  name: CommandSequence
  definition: Per-session monotonically increasing integer counter. Allocates the
    next seq for each new command. Determines the output file name prefix zero-padded
    to 6 digits (NNNNNN). Unique within a session; not global.
  properties:
  - Monotonic; never decreases or reuses values within a session
  - Zero-padded to 6 digits for output file names
  - Allocation happens before the queue job is created
  - seq is the stable external reference for a command within a session
  source_ranges:
  - start: 476
    end: 495
- concept_id: C-008
  name: OutputStore
  definition: Manages per-command output files NNNNNN.stdout.log, NNNNNN.stderr.log,
    and NNNNNN.meta.json. Provides read (offset+bytes), tail (last N lines), and regex
    search operations. Enforces path containment; rejects stream names other than
    stdout/stderr and path traversal attempts.
  properties:
  - stdout and stderr are stored in separate files; no combined output file
  - Read supports offset and max_bytes limits from config
  - Tail reads last N lines without loading the full file into memory
  - Search enforces max_matches limit
  - Rejects invalid stream names and path traversal via seq reference
  - Files are created empty before the queue job starts; written by worker
  - terminal_stat returns file sizes without reading full content
  source_ranges:
  - start: 461
    end: 495
  - start: 636
    end: 660
  - start: 661
    end: 725
  - start: 782
    end: 860
- concept_id: C-009
  name: TerminalExecutionJob
  definition: Queue job that performs the actual container execution. Receives session_id,
    project_id, seq, execution_kind, command or argv, cwd, mode, network, image_profile,
    and timeout. Starts sandbox container, redirects stdout and stderr to output files,
    updates CommandRecord and queue state on completion, failure, stop, or timeout.
    Removes container after execution.
  properties:
  - Never runs synchronously in the request handler
  - Writes stdout to NNNNNN.stdout.log and stderr to NNNNNN.stderr.log only
  - Updates NNNNNN.meta.json and history.jsonl entry on completion
  - Updates queue job status to completed, failed, or stopped
  - Stops and removes container regardless of outcome (cleanup_always)
  - Not exposed as a public MCP command
  source_ranges:
  - start: 26
    end: 44
  - start: 761
    end: 782
- concept_id: C-010
  name: ContainerRuntime
  definition: Creates and runs sandbox containers with fixed /workspace mount. Enforces
    non-root user, capability drop, no-new-privileges, resource limits (memory, cpus,
    pids), network policy, and read-only root filesystem. Supports rootless Docker
    or Podman.
  properties:
  - /workspace is always the container mount point; caller cannot choose it
  - 'Mount modes: read_only (ro), workspace_write (rw), scratch_write (ro + scratch
    rw)'
  - --cap-drop ALL and --security-opt no-new-privileges enforced by default
  - 'Resource limits: memory, cpus, pids_limit sourced from ConfigOverlay'
  - 'Network: none by default; package_registry via allowlisted egress only'
  - 'Forbidden: --privileged, host pid/network/ipc/uts namespaces, Docker socket'
  - Rootless Docker or Podman recommended but not required for MVP
  source_ranges:
  - start: 168
    end: 241
  - start: 242
    end: 275
  - start: 336
    end: 399
- concept_id: C-011
  name: QueueResultSemantics
  definition: Invariant governing interpretation of queue job completion versus terminal
    command success. Queue completed (progress=100) means the worker executed the
    full lifecycle. Terminal success additionally requires exit_code==0 and timed_out==false.
    terminal_get_status exposes both states.
  properties:
  - queue completed does not imply terminal success
  - Callers must inspect exit_code and timed_out; not only queue status
  - 'terminal_get_status returns: job_id, queue_status, terminal_status, exit_code,
    timed_out, output file names, and output byte sizes'
  source_ranges:
  - start: 761
    end: 782
  - start: 907
    end: 930
- concept_id: C-012
  name: AuditRecord
  definition: Immutable record created for every terminal_run invocation regardless
    of outcome. Contains full execution context including run_id, project_id, session_id,
    seq, command, resolved path hash, cwd, mode, network, image_profile, container_id,
    timing, exit_code, timed_out, output file names and sizes, policy decision summary,
    and error code.
  properties:
  - Created for both successful and failed executions
  - Must not record secret environment variable values
  - Distinct from CommandRecord; AuditRecord is the security trail
  source_ranges:
  - start: 858
    end: 887
- concept_id: C-013
  name: ConfigOverlay
  definition: Terminal-specific configuration layered on top of adapter SimpleConfig.
    Generator extends adapter SimpleConfigGenerator with terminal sections. Validator
    extends adapter SimpleConfigValidator with terminal-specific checks. CLI exposes
    generate, validate, and help subcommands.
  properties:
  - Must call adapter generator/validator first, then terminal-specific layer
  - 'Required terminal config sections: terminal.sessions, terminal.output, terminal.commands,
    terminal.cleanup, runtime'
  - terminal.sessions.ttl_seconds is required; rejected if missing or non-positive
  - default_history_limit must not exceed max_history_limit
  - max_sessions_per_project must be >= 1 and max_commands_per_session must be >=
    1
  source_ranges:
  - start: 782
    end: 858
  - start: 1097
    end: 1141
- concept_id: C-014
  name: PublicCommandSet
  definition: The complete set of public MCP commands exposed by mcp_terminal. All
    commands carry the terminal_ prefix. No short aliases are exposed. Commands are
    registered via the adapter register_custom_commands_hook mechanism.
  properties:
  - 'Commands: terminal_sessions, terminal_session_create, terminal_run, terminal_list,
    terminal_get, terminal_read, terminal_search_commands, terminal_search_output,
    terminal_tail, terminal_stat, terminal_delete, terminal_get_status'
  - 'Forbidden public aliases: list, delete, grep, tail, head, stat'
  - terminal_run returns job_id, seq, stdout_file, stderr_file, meta_file
  - terminal_list default limit is 25 in descending timestamp order
  - terminal_delete requires session_id; project_id is optional
  - terminal_stat returns metadata and output sizes only; no full file read
  source_ranges:
  - start: 461
    end: 495
  - start: 549
    end: 761
  - start: 930
    end: 970
